		'1' : '"Naturalmente mais Jovem" explains how the Biojovem project is, based on a successful case study and personal experiences of researcher and nutritional therapist Roxy Dillon, which will reveal which foods, herbs, supplements and oils help to age with more health and beauty. This is one of the best releases to read for those looking for a better quality of life without having to deprive themselves of mealtime.',
		'2' : 'A tragedy changes everything in the lives of the sisters Josie and Meredith. Sadness becomes something recurring, but they do everything they can to move on. And follow ... FiTFeen years later, Josie and Meredith do not have a harmonious relationship. Their differences of personality, which already existed before the tragedy, are even more pronounced. They see each other oTFen, but they do not understand each other. A life marked by veiled sadness and secrets that keep them away. Will Josie and Meredith be able to break free from their fears and open up to the new? Will they finally be able to move on really? Love first is a fascinating story about family, friendship and the courage to follow ones heart.',
		'3' : 'In this daily look of his life since A Work in Progress, Connor talks about his battles with clinical depression, social anxiety, self-love and acceptance; Your desire to keep an authentic self in a world that values parts and tastes about true connections; Their struggles with love and loss; And your renewed efforts to be in the moment - with others and with yourself. Said through short essays, letters to his past and future, poetry and original photography, Note to Self is an unprecedented look at the fascinating moment of the inner life of a young creator who heads inward to move forward.',
		'4' : 'In this in-depth book of life beyond the camera, Connor Franta shares the lessons he has learned on his journey from the kid in the small town to the feel of the Internet - until now. Here, Connor takes a look at his midwestern education as one of four children in the house and one of five in the classroom; His struggles with identity, body image and sexuality in his teens; And his decision to finally pursue his creative and artistic passions in his early twenties, creating his exciting career as a YouTube personality, philanthropist, entrepreneur and designer. Exploring his past with insight and humor, his giTF with humility, and his future with hope, Connor reveals his private struggles, while offering words of sincere wisdom to young adults. Your words resonate with anyone who grows old in the digital age, but at the core is a timeless message for people of all ages: do not be afraid to be yourself and to follow what you really want.  This color collection includes photography and childhood clippings provided by Connor and is a must-see for anyone inspired by their journey.',
		'5' : 'While we are witnessing a huge leap in the contingent of refugees knocking at the door of Europe in search of asylum, walls are hastily erected to avoid them. In this brief and current book, Zygmunt Bauman analyzes the origins, contours, and impact of fear that something terrible might threaten the well-being of society. The author dissects the dread provoked by the migrations and the dehumanization process of the newcomers. It also shows how politicians have exploited the fears and anxieties that have become widespread, especially among those who have already lost a lot - the excluded and the poor. Much more than a migratory crisis, we are experiencing a humanitarian crisis, says Bauman. And the only way to escape is to reject the treacherous temptations of separation, to acknowledge our growing interdependence as a species, and to find new ways of living together in solidarity and cooperation with those who may have opinions or preferences different from our own. Instead of walls, we need to build bridges.',
		'6' : 'Giverny is a world-renowned town that attracts crowds of tourists every year. ATFer all, Claude Monet, one of the greatest names in Impressionism, immortalized it in his paintings, with its gardens, the Japanese bridge and the nympheas in the pond. It is in this scenario that a respected physician is found dead, and the investigators in charge of the crime are entangled in a plot in which nothing is what it seems at first sight. As in an Impressionist canvas, the brushstrokes of the narrative are confused to, finally, give shape to a wraparound story of death and mystery in which each character is a puzzle to the part - mainly the protagonists. Three intense women, bound by mystery. An 11-year-old prodigy who dreams of being a great painter. The teacher of the only local school, who wants a true passion and new life, but is trapped in a marriage without love. And, at the center of it all, an old lady who watches the world from the top of her window.',
		'7' : 'Now, aTFer a number one on iTunes, nearly two million singles sold, live performances, where they shared the stage with Demi Lovato, Shawn Mendes and FiTFh Harmony and more than 26 million followers in all their Social media channels, Jack & Jack are on a wild ride - and they are not planning to slow down anytime soon. Fans will love reading about their journey from being two regular kids who grow up in Omaha, Nebraska, to the super-global world. Complete with never-before-seen photos, behind-the-scenes stories and entertaining personal anecdotes, You Do not Know Jacks is a privileged look at the lives of Jack & Jack, as the guys themselves said',
		'8' : 'For mega-star Demi Lovato. Life has been a journey - of striking achievements and sweeping losses. Record singer of sales. TV presenter and actress. She faced battles with depression and dependency. All without giving up finding happiness and herself. Demi shared her trajectory in the media. The lyrics of his songs and his 17 million followers on Twitter. These tweets have resulted in this book. A work in 365 honest insights. Hopeful and striking. Here they are. In Demis own words. The quotes that inspired her. As well as their personal reflections and goals. Demi Lovato - 365 days a year is for everyone. anywhere. That need comfort. Inspiration and a motive every day to be strong in their own trajectory.',
